task.summary: Default task
Another test commit

Look and Feel changed to Windows/Mac instead of Java
Menu bar added 'File' button added to menu bar 'New' and 'Open' added to 'File'
Other buttons like 'Exit' added to the 'File' menu
'Properties' opens a new window
Added classes for Network and Mesh
Pressing OK in Properties creates a window with the amount of nodes in a mesh configuration

The Network Settings panel sets the default values of the ComboBoxes to their value in the Network object Pressing OK sets the values of the Network object to those selected from the Comboboxes The Topology is then redrawn using the new values of the Network object
Properties window opens without being recreated if it's been opened before
Topology (for "mesh") is drawn properly
Can also draw topology for a "bus" network
Bus network is now made up of an array of Circle objects
Circles in a network have their number drawn inside them The circles are also clickable, currently listing their number when clicked
Added toolbar to the top of the window
Created a Flit class with get/set functions for the flit's location
Turned Network into an interface, and split its methods between Mesh, Bus, etc
Class made to create a window for the diagram of a router that's clicked on
Modified Flit class
Clicking a node creates a new window where a router diagram can be put
Channels added to router
Methods added to Mesh and Router
Clicking on a router in a Network Topology window opens a diagram of the router
The diagram now shows a single input channel and a single output channel
Clicking on a router in the topology diagram now opens a Router Diagram, with the correct channels depending on which router is selected
Next Cycle button calls nextCycle for each router Flits can be created
Flits can be input into a router, and they're stored in the correct channel
Clicking "Next Cycle" updates the image with new shapes
"Next Cycle" brings flits from the channels into "Route Computation"
"Next Cycle" moves flits out of the channel and cycles/displays flits as they move through the pipeline
Routers finish processing whole packets before moving on to the next channel
Packets now make it through the entire router, from the input channel out to the correct output channel
Packets can be passed between routers, and are randomly generated
Set back to a single packet instead of generated packets
JFrame is passed between objects but can't edit the text on the window
The text window is now created when Routers are created Key information during the simulation can be sent to the text window to display
Empty flit slots are now painted over with white rectangles to show they're empty Flit injection rate can be changed in the options window
Bus now works, and can send packets along the bus to the target Router
Torus route computation works correctly
